#: src/types.md:1
msgid "Types and Bounds"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:3
msgid "Single line formatting"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:5
msgid "`[T]` no spaces"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:6
msgid ""
"`[T; expr]`, e.g., `[u32; 42]`, `[Vec<Foo>; 10 * 2 + foo()]` (space after "
"colon, no spaces around square brackets)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:7
msgid "`*const T`, `*mut T` (no space after `*`, space before type)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:8
msgid ""
"`&'a T`, `&T`, `&'a mut T`, `&mut T` (no space after `&`, single spaces "
"separating other words)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:9
msgid ""
"`unsafe extern \"C\" fn<'a, 'b, 'c>(T, U, V) -> W` or `fn()` (single spaces "
"around keywords and sigils, and after commas, no trailing commas, no spaces "
"around brackets)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:10
msgid "`!` gets treated like any other type name, `Name`"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:11
msgid ""
"`(A, B, C, D)` (spaces after commas, no spaces around parens, no trailing "
"comma unless it is a one-tuple)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:12
msgid ""
"`<Baz<T> as SomeTrait>::Foo::Bar` or `Foo::Bar` or `::Foo::Bar` (no spaces "
"around `::` or angle brackets, single spaces around `as`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:13
msgid ""
"`Foo::Bar<T, U, V>` (spaces after commas, no trailing comma, no spaces "
"around angle brackets)"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:14
msgid "`T + T + T` (single spaces between types, and `+`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:15
msgid "`impl T + T + T` (single spaces between keyword, types, and `+`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:17
msgid "Do not put space around parentheses used in types, e.g., `(Foo)`"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:19
msgid "Line breaks"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:21
msgid ""
"Avoid breaking lines in types where possible. Prefer breaking at outermost "
"scope, e.g., prefer"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:30
msgid "to"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:39
msgid ""
"If a type requires line-breaks in order to fit, this section outlines where "
"to break such types if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:42
msgid "Break `[T; expr]` after the `;` if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:44
msgid "Break function types following the rules for function declarations."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:46
msgid "Break generic types following the rules for generics."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:48
msgid ""
"Break types with `+` by breaking before the `+` and block-indenting the "
"subsequent lines. When breaking such a type, break before _every_ `+`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:63
msgid "Precise capturing bounds"
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:65
msgid ""
"A `use<'a, T>` precise capturing bound is formatted as if it were a single "
"path segment with non-turbofished angle-bracketed args, like a trait bound "
"whose identifier is `use`."
msgstr ""

#: src/types.md:69
msgid "// is formatted analogously to:\n"
msgstr ""
